        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Macon Geo</placeName> <date>July 16 1849</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">I received this morning<lb/> the last Occident&#59; but as I do not find my name among the<lb/> receipt&#44; I apprehend that you have not received my subscription<lb/> yet. <persName>Mr Elias Block</persName> formerly from <placeName>Griffin</placeName> called on me<lb/> when he was about removing to <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> on the <date>6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of May</date><lb/> and I sent with him the Three Dollars. I request you respectfully<lb/> to cause an inquiry after him&#44; <persName>Mrsses Blum</persName> &#38; <persName>Simpson</persName> or<lb/> <persName>Arnolds</persName> could tell you where to find him.</p>
			<p>Be so kind as to remember me to <persName>Mr. Hackenburg</persName>&#44; I read<lb/> with sorrow the demise of his son <persName>Henry</persName>. Give him my<lb/> care&#44; May the Lord remember him to good&#44; and may he be<lb/> consoled&#33; I am your admirer and</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Brother in faith</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">A. Defsan</persName>.</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><hi rend="underline">past paid</hi></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Pa.</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
